				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Kiting on raids<a name="51198"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 04 7:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Was recently on a open TT raid where due to a shortage of rangers and druids I was designated to kite some of the adds that spawn from her...
<br />

<br />
As we understood it 4 mobs were supposed to spawn at 75%, some butterfly thingummies spawn at 50% and a final 4 mobs at 25%..
<br />

<br />
Well that was the way it was explained to us (unsure of the truth here)
<br />

<br />
We didnt get the spawn of 4 adds at 75% though the butterflies arrived on queue and we dealt with them...The 4 adds spawned at 25% health and so I try to get aggro... and keep trying...
<br />

<br />
I used BBB, DDD,SSoP and I think I even tried a charm! lol (desperate measure I know but I have got aggro from uncharmable mobs by trying to charm them anyway...)
<br />

<br />
The result was an add ripping into the casters and no aggro for me as usual...
<br />

<br />
How do you guys gain quick aggro for kiting spawned adds? I really have no idea at it would enhance greatly my utility/usefulness on raids...</span></td>
