				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting on raids<a name="51392"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 12:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At 75% a swarm of Dream Defilers show up.  You can get a second wave too - if you don't kill the first ones fast enough.  They look like nettling wraiths in PON but much smaller and hard to spot at first.  We AOE the suckers -- I load up a lute and hit them with melody of mischief to slow and DoT em -- they go down in a hurry.  At 50% TT debuffs 12 buffs off  your raid.  Some raid leaders have everyone but the main tank and a couple of healers run out of the dome ahead of this which is totally retarded and asking for problems.  Just have casters ready to MGB buffs back on and your entire raid can be rebuffed in 20 seconds.  Less chance the main tank and two healers are going to die alone.  At around 40% (sometimes later -- it doesn't seem consistent) the four gargoyles come to life.  Yes, you can kite them and it isn't that hard to do.  I have done it a time or two but we usually have knights do it unless we have plenty of healing in which case we just have spare tanks and shaman assigned to each garg to off-tank them.  They are slowable.  Seriously, the biggest test in this raid is getting melees to STOP hitting Terris at key moments.  This is one encounter where if your forces just zerg the boss, you will die an ugly, fast, painful death.  Knowing when NOT to be killing the boss is crucial to certain mobs like Terris, Saryn, and a few others.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
