				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Kiting on raids<a name="51630"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 13 04 11:17 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">the trick with running out is you generally want to do that with a raiding force you know and trust to do it right</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Exactly.
<br />

<br />
Steppy's first law of raid leadership -- the raid instructions that require the fewest number of people to change what they are doing are necessarily the best instructions.  Having 7 people cast MGB is guaranteed to be more efficient than having 35 people run out of the area en masse at the same time, then run back.
<br />

<br />
Yes, if people pay close attention to instructions, running out of the dome works fine.  But I always assume SOMEONE -- possibly multiple someones -- will miss every instruction I give.  Therefore, since the tank and healers who stay behind need to be re-buffed anyway, along with everyone who missed the boat, it just makes more sense to stay there and rebuff everyone, plus it gives you plenty of emergency healers and tanks if something goes wrong during the unbuffed period.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
